  "prompt": "What is best earphone under 500rs (in ear) with good sound quality in India?",
  "response": "Finding a good pair of in-ear earphones under \u20b9500 in India can be challenging, but there are a few options that offer decent sound quality and durability for the price. Here are some popular choices:\n\n### 1. **Boat BassHeads 100**\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b9399\n   - **Features:** Powerful bass, tangle-free flat cables, in-line mic, and remote.\n   - **Sound Quality:** Good for bass lovers, though mids and highs are average.\n\n### 2. **Realme Buds 2**\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b9399\n   - **Features:** Ergonomic design, in-line mic, and remote.\n   - **Sound Quality:** Balanced sound with decent bass, mids, and highs.\n\n### 3. **JBL Endurance Run**\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b9499\n   - **Features:** Comfortable fit, sweatproof design, in-line mic, and remote.\n   - **Sound Quality:** Good overall sound with clear mids and highs, and adequate bass.\n\n### 4. **Sony MDR-EX150AP**\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b9499\n   - **Features:** Comfortable fit, in-line mic, and remote.\n   - **Sound Quality:** Balanced sound with clear mids and highs, and decent bass.\n\n### 5. **Mi Earphone Basic**\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b9399\n   - **Features:** Lightweight design, in-line mic, and remote.\n   - **Sound Quality:** Clear and balanced sound, suitable for everyday use.\n\n### 6. **OPPO O-Fresh M31**\n   - **Price:** Around \u20b9499\n   - **Features:** Stylish design, in-line mic, and remote.\n   - **Sound Quality:** Good bass and clear mids and highs.\n\n### Things to Consider:\n- **Sound Preference:** If you prefer bass-heavy sound, go for Boat BassHeads 100 or Realme Buds 2. For a more balanced sound, Sony MDR-EX150AP or Mi Earphone Basic might be better.\n- **Build Quality:** Look for tangle-free cables and durable materials, especially if you plan to use them frequently.\n- **Comfort:** Ensure the ear tips fit well and are comfortable for extended use.\n\nWhile these earphones are budget-friendly, they may not match the sound quality of higher-end models. However, they offer good value for money and are suitable for casual listening and everyday use.",
